com.paypal.merchant.sdk.domain
Interface TransactionExtras

public interface TransactionExtras

When taking a payment you can specify some extra data that will be stored in the paypal system.

These include the payment due date, the payment terms, the payer's email, the billing and shipping
information, etc. You can fill out as much of this as you want. For example, it's ok to specify the
shipping information yet still leave the due date unset.

App developers can also store a string of its choosing called the merchant string. This
will be stored along with the transaction. When calling up a list of historical PayPal transactions
the merchant is able to read this string back. This allows you to store whatever IDs or string you
wish into the PayPal transaction.

To create a new TransactionExtras object you can use DomainFactory.newTransactionExtras().

setMerchantString

void setMerchantString(String str)
Sets the app-developer defined 'merchant string'.
Allows app developers to set an arbitrary string to be saved with this transaction.
When calling up historical transactions the application will be able to recall this string.
The format of any data stored in this string is up to the 3rd party developer.

Parameters:
str - A String
